The Lagos State Government has in line with its new policy of naming and shaming convicted sex offenders, published the identities of two sex offenders.The sex offenders are Mr Gbenga Olasunkanmi and Mr Basiru Obasekere.Olasunkanmi was on November 30, 2021, sentenced to life imprisonment by the Lagos High Court for the offence of defilement, while Obasekere was also sentenced to life imprisonment for a similar offence.This was disclosed to journalists by the Executive Secretary of the Lagos State Domestic and Sexual Violence Agency (DSVA), Mrs Titilola Vivour Adeniyi during a press conference at the agency's office on Thursday.The details according to the Executive Secretary will include name and picture of the sex offender, nature of the offence as well as the duration of the sentence handed down by the court.Mrs Vivour Adeniyi noted that this was in line with the provisions of the Domestic and Sexual Violence Agency Law, particularly section 42 which provides that the Agency is to periodically publish details of Sex convicts in the state.She also said letters of advisory have been issued to local governments and traditional rulers of the communities where the convicts previously resided.“This measure is one amongst many deployed by the state government to end the culture of impunity and also serve as a deterrence to other sex offenders.“As further provided in the law, the details of sex convicts are to be published periodically on the State Government’s website, (www.lagosstate.gov.ng), the website of the Ministry of Justice (https://lagosstatemoj.org) and the Agency’s website; (www.dsvrtlagos.org)“The Executive Security reiterated that the stance of the State government is resolute in preventing incidents of sexual and domestic abuse, whilst ensuring justice for all survivors.“She added that to report any case of domestic and sexual violence, Lagosians are to call the toll-free number, 08000333333,” a statement by the agency said.